Pak doesn't support inline C directly. Instead, write a separate .c file and call it via extern:

**fast_math.c:**
```c
#include <libdragon.h>

// fast inverse square root (N64 has no FPU sqrt)
float fast_invsqrt(float x) {
    float xhalf = 0.5f * x;
    int i = *(int*)&x;
    i = 0x5f3759df - (i >> 1);
    x = *(float*)&i;
    x = x * (1.5f - xhalf * x * x);
    return x;
}
```

**game.pak:**
```pak
extern "C" {
    fn fast_invsqrt(x: f32) -> f32
}

fn normalize_2d(x: *f32, y: *f32) {
    let len_sq: f32 = (*x) * (*x) + (*y) * (*y)
    if len_sq > 0.0001 {
        let inv: f32 = fast_invsqrt(len_sq)
        *x = (*x) * inv
        *y = (*y) * inv
    }
}
```

Link the .c file in your Makefile. Pak and C objects link together normally.

